title: Grateful Dead Live at Saratoga Performing Arts Center on 1983-06-18
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi DR-2 > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC 2448 tagged. Transferred by Andrew F. 03/2012
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Jack Straw, Bird Song, Mexicali Blues-> Big River, Althea, Hell In A Bucket-> Deal

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band Reprise-> Morning Dew, Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away-> Touch Of Gray, E:Don't Ease Me In-> E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
SPAC info... Tripping down memory lane this morning. Missed this fantastic show though friends all raved about it and the lightning storm during Wheel… This appears (sounds) the best of the audience recordings but I haven't spent too much time on them. Shame there are no Soundboards. 
I searched attendance info on SPAC and while The Who set a record in 71 (~31K) GD set the "all time" record 1985 (w 40K) causing management to place a cap on attendance. 1985 was the 3rd straight year they broke or nearly broke the records for the venue. (31K in 83, 37K in 84)

THIS is the best copy of this show! Definitely the best copy of this stellar show and one of the craziest Scarlet>Fires of all time. Jerry is at his very best during this Scarlet solo, I mean the ebb and flow and Phil dropping bombs! It's flipping insane and the solo runs at least 2 min like they tended to do from 82-84. AMAZING Morning Dew! A very long PITB (for 83) at 18+ min...83 GD is Great, and sure Jerry's voice had many 'croaky' nights  from 83-85 but you just gotta ignore that and let it go cuz musically these years are as intense and interesting as any other, 80-82 as well but Jerry's voice was better and more consistent in those years...
